  <p>
    We use <m>\mathbb{R}^2</m>
    (pronounced <q>r two</q>)
    to represent all the vectors in the plane,
    and use <m>\mathbb{R}^3</m>
    (pronounced <q>r three</q>)
    to represent all the vectors in space.
        <idx><h>r@<m>\mathbb{R}</m></h></idx>
  </p>

